@startuml dkey_access_to_smk_immobilizer_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title DKEY Access To SMK Immobilizer Signal Flow\n(DKEY access publication -> SMK immobilizer/key-auth state)

participant "DKEY\naccess-state producer" as DKEY #E8F7E8
participant "Vehicle state\nDriveState visibility" as Veh #E8F0FE
participant "SMK\nimmobilizer owner" as SMK #FFF4CC
participant "Immobilizer bus /\nobservers" as Obs #FCE8FF

== Access Inputs ==

DKEY -> SMK : frmDigitalKeyStateMsg\nVehicleAccessState / KeyPresence
Veh -> SMK : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\nDriveState
activate SMK
SMK -> SMK : normalize DKEY / vehicle stale inputs
SMK -> SMK : accessAuthorized =\nKeyPresence == 1 && VehicleAccessState >= 1
SMK -> SMK : derive ImmobilizerState / KeyAuthState
note right of SMK
Representative inputs
- VehicleAccessState
- KeyPresence
- DriveState

Representative outputs
- ImmobilizerState
- KeyAuthState
end note

== Immobilizer Publish ==

SMK -> Obs : frmImmobilizerStateMsg
SMK -> Obs : traceable SMK auth / immo state
deactivate SMK

note over DKEY, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. DKEY publishes access state and key presence
2. SMK combines that with current drive state
3. SMK derives immobilizer and key-auth state
4. Downstream observers and tests verify authorization readiness
end note

@enduml
